Package modelCheckCTL.model

Interface Summary
Model  
ModelListener Registered with the view.
 

Class Summary
AbstractModel  
AdjacencyList This was taken from wiki-algorithm
CTLFormula This is the element of a binary search tree that will represent a CTL formula.
CTLFormulaStack This class is responsible for creating a data structure to represent a well formed CTL formula.
CTLParser This is the main object for creating and handling a CTL formula.
Edge  
KripkeElement The kripke structure will be a graph, each state in the graph can have transitions to many states and from many states but there should not be duplicates.
KripkeStruct The parser will take a text file that describes a kripke structure and build a directed graph.
LabelCTLAlg This object brings together the kripke structure the formula and the starting state to determine if a current formula holds or if it fails for a given model.
ModelCheckCTLModel The model will create a directed graph to represent the kripke structure Parse and simplify a CTL formula and set the starting state and label the kripke structure to find out if it is satisfied.
ModelEvent This allows communication with the view.
Node  
ParenthesesCheck This class checks all parentheses but we only use ( or [ type parentheses.
TarjanAlg This was slightly modified to handle the case where a node does not have any transitions.
 

Exception Summary
ModelException Exception thrown by the model.
